text: Dryosaurids were primitive iguanodonts from the Middle Jurassic to the Lower Cretaceous. They are found in what is now Africa, Europe, and North America. There are 11 genera, of which Dryosaurus is the best known. == References == Category:iguanodonts Category:Jurassic dinosaurs Category:Cretaceous dinosaurs
title: Dryosauridae
